cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is primarily focused on improving the training of deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) using Batch Normalization (BN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper extensively experiments on image classification tasks (CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper proposes a new technique called Mixture Normalization (MN), which involves disentangling sub-populations and independently normalizing them. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling of data distributions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Sound).
